      },
      "date": "2024-10-18 23:19:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> Since conf-sanity test 32* are for upgrade testing with old version\n > disk images, can we just skip the subtests under interop\n > configuration with MDS server that is >=v2_15_65-31-g74a5b9efaaec?\n\nIt might be OK if that change was only done on b2_15, otherwise it would disable all of these tests forever into the future.\n\nThe real problem looks like the test added some checking that is run on the b2_15 client (fscrypt filename encryption?) for a feature that is not present/working properly on b2_15?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
